<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The macro takes the address of the supplied token expression: & (tok). In OS_GenericBinSemTake_Impl the call is OS_OBJECT_TABLE_GET(..., *token) where token is declared const OS_object_token_t *token. That yields a const OS_object_token_t * being passed to OS_ObjectIndexFromToken via OS_OBJECT_TABLE_GET. If OS_ObjectIndexFromToken is declared to take a non-const OS_object_token_t * (i.e. it does not use a pointer-to-const), this discards the const qualifier and thus violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13. A fix is to declare OS_ObjectIndexFromToken to take const OS_object_token_t * (or otherwise preserve const qualification).
</scenario>
